Most economists at leading banks
want to widen the role of euro-area bailout funds, Financial
Times Deutschland reported, citing a survey.  Twenty-two of 26 economists who commented on the subject as
part of the survey were in favor of direct recapitalization of
ailing banks by the funds, FTD said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
